buses of ancient history, the imaginative functions of the monarchy, and fantasies of Anglo-Saxon global domination. They are followed by illuminating studies of prominent thinkers, including J. A. Hobson, L. T. Hobhouse, John Stuart Mill, Henry Sidgwick, Herbert Spencer, and J. R. Seeley. While insisting that liberal attitudes to empire were multiple and varied, Bell emphasizes the liberal fascination with settler colonialism. It was in the settler empire that many liberal imperialists found the place of their political dreams.Reordering the World is a significant contribution to the history of modern political thought and political theory.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aImperialismxHistory. 0aLiberalismzGreat BritainxHistory. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political Ideologies / Conservatism & Liberalism.2bisacsh  aAnglo-American.  aAnglo-world supremacy.  aBritish empire.  aE. A. Freeman.  aEdwardian era.  aHenry Sidgwick.  aHerbert Spencer.  aIndia.  aIreland.  aJ. A. Froude.  aJ. A. Hobson.  aJohn Robert Seeley.  aJohn Stuart Mill.  aL. T. Hobhouse.  aQueen Victoria.  aT. H. Green.  aUnited States.  aVictorian era.  acolonialism.  acolonization.  aconquest.  aconstitutional patriotism.  adomestic politics.  aempire.  aglobal order.  aglobalization.  agovernance.  ahistorians.  ahistorical time.  aideology.  aimperial federation.  aimperial ideology.  aimperial imaginary.  aimperial rule.  aimperial thinker.  aimperial thought.  aimperialism.  aimperialists.  ainternational society.  ainternationalism.  ajustification.  aliberal civilizational model.  aliberal imperialism.  aliberal political thought.  aliberal thinkers.  aliberal thought.  aliberalism.  aliberals.  aliberty.  amonarchy.  anation.  anationalist co